description.narrative:
1)  Provide safe water to 1,261 people by building infrastructure for water capture and storage;
2) Improve the hygiene of 400 people by installing ventilated dry pit latrines;
3) Strengthen four Water and Sanitation Committees (CAPS) to ensure sustainable management of water systems;
4)  Promote a change in the knowledge, attitudes, behaviors and practices of 4,259 people on hygiene and environmental sanitation, involving schools, community leaders and CAPS members during this process.

The project's goal is to improve the quality of life for families in the districts of Yucul, San Pablo and El Horno (municipality of San Ramón, Matagalpa), through the provision or improvement of water and sanitation infrastructure, through 4 objectives: 
1)  Provide safe water to 1,261 people by building infrastructure for water capture and storage;
2) Improve the hygiene of 400 people by installing ventilated dry pit latrines;
3) Strengthen four Water and Sanitation Committees (CAPS) to ensure sustainable management of water systems;
4)  Promote a change in the knowledge, attitudes, behaviors and practices of 4,259 people on hygiene and environmental sanitation, involving schools, community leaders and CAPS members during this process.
